    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-13T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-13T06:00:00-05:00" n="232"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.2 A 2/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-13T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1927—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. My 138, December 28, 3 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d232fn30">Not printed.</note>
                    Letter from League Secretariat states that on January 12th experts on double
                    taxation decided to hold next meeting in London on April 4th, 1927, and have
                    expressed the hope that an expert from the United States will take part in that
                        meeting.<note n="31" xml:id="d232fn31">The United States had not been
                        represented at the meeting of the Committee of Experts on Double Taxation
                        and Tax Evasion at Geneva on Jan. 5, 1927.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Secretariat requests to be informed as soon as possible of name of American
                    expert so that formal invitation may be sent him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
